                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/105: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-24T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 24, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>144. The information transmitted in Department’s No. 127 should answer all
                    queries in the mind of the French Foreign Office.</p>
                <p>Their statement “that they are not at all convinced that the wolfram and antimony
                    in question were purchased by the United States Government” has no foundation
                    whatsoever. It was purchased as reported.</p>
                <p>We greatly hope Foreign Office will reach a favorable decision in this matter
                    promptly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
